            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-23T09:31:13+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-23T09:31:13+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-23T00:01:13Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-23T00:01:13Z">
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A strong high pressure system east of Tasmania will maintain a ridge over SA this week. A cold front will pass over the south on Saturday, weakening and clearing in the east early Sunday. A new high pressure system will develop in the Bight on Sunday, slowly drifting to the southeast on Monday while continuing to extend a ridge over SA.</text>
                <text type="preamble">Wind and wave forecasts are averages. Wind gusts can be 40 per cent stronger than the forecast, and stronger still in squalls and thunderstorms. Maximum waves can be twice the forecast height.</text>
